review:
I don't typically write reviews, but this game aged like milk and I just couldn't skip not sharing my opinion of it. I played this as a kid and I thought I'd pick this up when it comes on sale to relive some of those "good" memories I've had of it. As soon as I launched the game I knew it was going to be a shit show and here's how I got to that conclusion.

What went wrong:
- the menu's text is at very low opacity and I had to pop the steam overlay on and off just so the text would fade in a little bit to make out what I had to do, a problem that I have no clue on how to fix to this day;
- playing this when you have a multi monitor setup is awful as the cursor isn't locked on the monitor where the game is currently being played on (despite running the game in fullscreen);
- running the game at more than it's native 30 fps is going to give you all sorts of glitches (within the first minute I noticed my first glitch where I couldn't reverse the car if I had more than the locked 30 fps);
- the game itself is a terrible port of the console versions and I noticed it as soon as I aimed down the sights of weapons and the crosshair would just move around if I pressed the move controls (WASD);
- cars are made out of paper plates where if you crash it ever so slightly it already starts to smoke and it takes no more than 3-4 crashes to make it burn and eventually explode; 
- the suspension of some cars make it near impossible to take a turn without flipping them in the process;
- dumb AI that has no idea what to do in some scenario (like shooting at an enemy ahead of them if you're slightly out of range);
- trash AI pathing where the drivers would often miss an opening and would just grind against the wall trying to reach the destination despite it obviously not working;
- overpowered weapons that take less than half a second to kill you (I'm looking at you M4);
- missions that make no sense from the point of view of progression, at least in the beginning (feels like it's a game revolved around random missions instead of following somewhat of a story);
- really stupid enemy faction system where you often can't complete certain quests because they involve you passing through said territories and at any point an idiot with a combat shotgun can insta-destroy your vehicle;
- awful main character who would betray his own mother for a penny;
- mission timers that often are barely enough to complete them without re-trying;
- inability to check the map and this is really stupid considering some of the missions take place on a different island than where you took it from so you keep driving towards the mission until you realize you're near the ocean and it's on another freakin' island so you have to change your route 'cus the connection between them is on the side of the island.

The list would be endless if I had to write everything down, but these are the main problems that I couldn't get over. If you're looking to relive those childhood memories by replaying this game, don't. Let them be memories of what you thought at the time was a great game. I can not recommend this game despite trying time and time again to give it another chance at redemption, but the further I progress, the more I'm disappointed.

This is an amazing game, the one that single-handed started the open world action genre. Its importance is not to be underestimated, and the game is still highly playable even nowadays.

This Steam version is not bad at all; I've been able to play just like I did with my old retail version, and, as a matter of fact, even better due to controller support, higher resolution and new TV.

Now, this is a recommended game, but beware of:
- This game is full of things to do but NOT as much as basically any other game in the franchise. So, if you like GTA 5, for example, bear in mind that this game is far simpler, with "to dos" that look more like work than fun sometimes;
- I needed a patch for dark cars and a mod for the controllers to work like they did for the PS2. The game is playable without then, especially if you are using mouse+kb, but be prepared for some tweaks before playing in case you need it;
- If you plan to make a 100% playthrough, use a guide. There are missables in this game, and you will be very dissatisfied if you discover that you missed one of them 30 hours in.

